cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR. 

This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on the task of recognizing implicit discourse relations in Chinese text. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses a recurrent neural network with attention, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses a partial sampling scheme, which is a technique commonly used in neural network optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with text classification and information retrieval, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
